The paper deals with a fundamental problem in combinatorial group testing, which involves designing efficient algorithms for identifying positive items in a set using as few tests as possible. This problem is closely related to several areas of computer science, including discrete mathematics (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and combinatorial optimization (cs.CG). Given the focus of the paper on disjunct matrices, which are a key tool in group testing, it is likely to be classified under cs.DM. However, the paper also involves theoretical analysis of algorithms and optimization techniques, which could lead to classification under the other categories as well.
